WEBVTT

00:00.055 --> 00:02.023
<i>Back in the '90s, there was no teacher</i>

00:02.078 --> 00:04.187
<i>who looked out more for
the students of William Penn</i>

00:04.254 --> 00:05.281
<i>than Coach Mellor.</i>

00:05.359 --> 00:06.558
<i>Even outside of gym class,</i>

00:06.627 --> 00:08.660
<i>he was always there
to lend a helping hand.</i>

00:08.762 --> 00:10.962
<i>And he was constantly
pushing them to eat healthier</i>

00:11.031 --> 00:13.064
<i>and fuel their brains for learning.</i>

00:13.133 --> 00:15.700
<i>Yep, it was safe to say Coach loved
helping every kid at school.</i>

00:15.769 --> 00:16.801
Oh, I totally forgot.

00:16.870 --> 00:18.236
I have to get to the DMV
right after school,

00:18.338 --> 00:19.671
but Toby has Chess Club.

00:19.740 --> 00:23.274
Don't worry. Your knight will
move young Toby to Castle Julie.

00:23.343 --> 00:26.244
Another problem checkmated
by "Rook" Mellor.

00:26.346 --> 00:27.479
I love you,

00:27.547 --> 00:30.015
but sometimes I wish
you'd talk normally.

00:30.083 --> 00:32.450
<i>Yep, he and Toby were spending
more and more time together,</i>

00:32.552 --> 00:34.152
<i>and their relationship was blossoming.</i>

00:34.221 --> 00:36.488
Jeff Gordon hugs the corner!

00:36.556 --> 00:38.289
Crew Chief Toby, what's my next move?

00:38.392 --> 00:39.557
Uh, drive really fast!

00:39.626 --> 00:41.826
Takin' her up to 35, baby!

00:42.963 --> 00:44.729
Eat my dust, power walkers!

00:44.765 --> 00:47.132
<i>And Coach even lent his
style of help with homework.</i>

00:47.200 --> 00:49.567
As the Confederates blitzed
from both sides,

00:49.670 --> 00:51.636
the Union Army rushed up the middle.

00:51.705 --> 00:54.506
And just when you thought they'd
fumble at Gettysburg... Boom!

00:54.574 --> 00:58.009
The Union scooped up the loose
ball and took it to the house!

00:58.078 --> 00:59.435
Appomattox Courthouse.

00:59.489 --> 01:00.745
Suck it, Robert E. Lee!

01:00.814 --> 01:03.648
<i>It was clear Coach was becoming
more than just a coach to Toby,</i>

01:03.750 --> 01:05.083
<i>and Julie was thrilled.</i>

01:05.152 --> 01:07.018
<i>Until one day,
something happened at school</i>

01:07.076 --> 01:08.128
<i>that changed everything.</i>

01:08.201 --> 01:10.755
Okay, today we finish "Macbeth."

01:10.802 --> 01:12.223
It is the big final fight

01:12.292 --> 01:14.726
between our protagonist and Macduff.

01:14.828 --> 01:17.295
- The crime dog?
- That is McGruff.

01:17.397 --> 01:20.331
But we're gonna take a bite
out of Shakespeare

01:20.400 --> 01:22.400
with the help from our young thespians,

01:22.502 --> 01:23.802
Toby and Hunter!

01:23.870 --> 01:25.837
Just like we rehearsed, guys.
Here we go.

01:25.939 --> 01:29.374
"Of all men else I have avoided thee.

01:29.443 --> 01:31.142
But get thee back!

01:31.211 --> 01:34.846
My soul is too much charged
with blood of thine already!"

01:34.948 --> 01:35.980
Oh, snap!

01:36.049 --> 01:37.782
I know. Shakespeare gets me going, too.

01:37.851 --> 01:40.151
- What the hell's going on here?
- Inspiring my students, Rick.

01:40.253 --> 01:42.120
- To beat the crap out of each other?!
- Oh...

01:42.222 --> 01:44.516
Hey! This is not what we rehearsed!

01:44.955 --> 01:47.859
<i>♪ One of these days,
you're gonna get outta here ♪</i>

01:47.961 --> 01:50.829
<i>♪ Live your life and finally be free ♪</i>

01:50.931 --> 01:53.798
<i>♪ Go where you wanna go,
do what you wanna do ♪</i>

01:53.900 --> 01:57.331
<i>♪ Someday, you will say
"Those were the days" ♪</i>

01:57.394 --> 01:59.433
<i>It was March 18th, 1990-something,</i>

01:59.495 --> 02:00.925
<i>and I was feeling overwhelmed</i>

02:01.003 --> 02:02.741
<i>by everything I had to do
for the music department.</i>

02:02.843 --> 02:03.842
Hi.

02:03.944 --> 02:05.009
Look at this schedule.

02:05.112 --> 02:06.611
It's jam-packed with classes.

02:06.713 --> 02:08.413
Leading jazz band. Quakers Dozen.

02:08.514 --> 02:10.181
And our musicals
have been so successful,

02:10.282 --> 02:12.350
Glascott wants us to do two this year.

02:12.452 --> 02:13.551
- Oh, please tell me one of them is...
- And no, neither of them are...

02:13.653 --> 02:14.822
..."You're a Good Man, Charlie Brown."

02:14.900 --> 02:16.421
- Darn!
- You gotta stop asking, buddy.

02:16.523 --> 02:17.489
Fine. For now.

02:17.591 --> 02:18.656
God, how did this happen?

02:18.759 --> 02:19.728
When I started here,

02:19.807 --> 02:21.693
all I taught was Music One
and Intro to the Recorder.

02:21.795 --> 02:23.094
Well, it happened 'cause of you.

02:23.196 --> 02:25.396
Since you started, you've inspired
so many kids to love music

02:25.499 --> 02:27.121
that everyone wants to get involved.

02:27.183 --> 02:29.734
I mean, look at you.
You are a rock star.

02:29.810 --> 02:30.810
Maybe in my younger days.

02:30.904 --> 02:32.370
Once a rock star, always a rock star.

02:32.472 --> 02:34.506
Well, we did open for
Terence Trent D'Arby once.

02:34.608 --> 02:35.940
Oh! TTD!

02:36.042 --> 02:39.110
Maybe I can move Show Choir
rehearsal to later in the day.

02:39.212 --> 02:41.379
Or you could ask one of us to cover
for you until you get there.

02:41.481 --> 02:43.248
Great idea. So, can I
count on you tomorrow?

02:43.350 --> 02:45.216
Can't. I got a podiatrist appointment.

02:45.318 --> 02:47.519
I've got this one toe...
I don't know what's going on,

02:47.621 --> 02:50.789
- but flip-flops are a no-can-do.
- Uh-huh.

02:53.293 --> 02:54.392
Hey, Wilma. You got a minute?

02:54.494 --> 02:56.261
Now that I got all these
chemicals cooking here,

02:56.363 --> 02:57.595
I have exactly that.

02:57.697 --> 02:59.264
Anything longer,
you're gonna wanna wear a mask.

02:59.366 --> 03:01.032
So, as you know,
I've been working really hard

03:01.134 --> 03:02.267
to expand the music program.

03:02.369 --> 03:03.701
So proud of you. 50 seconds left.

03:03.804 --> 03:05.470
Well, the music department's
become really busy,

03:05.572 --> 03:06.738
and I've got a lot on my plate,

03:06.840 --> 03:08.573
so can you cover the first half
of Show Choir this week?

03:08.675 --> 03:09.688
It's super easy.

03:09.782 --> 03:11.943
It's mostly just kids in sequin
vests singing soft rock hits

03:12.045 --> 03:13.812
while awkwardly stepping
from side-to-side.

03:13.914 --> 03:14.979
Sometimes snapping gently.

03:15.081 --> 03:16.581
I do love snapping. 15 seconds.

03:16.683 --> 03:17.816
I know you're super busy, too...

03:17.918 --> 03:19.951
I am. Ten seconds.
But don't worry. I got you.

03:20.053 --> 03:21.386
Thank you! You're such a good friend.

03:21.488 --> 03:23.588
I know. Three. Two.

03:23.690 --> 03:25.156
Oh, [bleep]! You're serious!

03:25.258 --> 03:27.325
<i>As I was racing out of Wilma's class,</i>

03:27.427 --> 03:28.726
<i>Julie and Coach were in the midst</i>

03:28.829 --> 03:30.228
<i>of some urgent business of their own.</i>

03:30.330 --> 03:31.663
I can't believe Toby got in a fight.

03:31.765 --> 03:33.131
The other kid had to have started it.

03:33.233 --> 03:35.433
Hunter has been known to be
somewhat of a bully.

03:35.535 --> 03:37.168
Please don't tell him I said that.

03:37.270 --> 03:40.705
CB was definitely playing with
fire when he handed him this.

03:40.807 --> 03:44.042
It's a novelty sword from the
Medieval Times dinner theater.

03:44.144 --> 03:47.071
Jousting, fair maidens,
a nice piece of meat.

03:47.141 --> 03:48.179
It's a good value.

03:48.281 --> 03:49.948
That's what I hear. I've been
meaning to check it out.

03:50.050 --> 03:51.482
You will not be disappointed.

03:51.585 --> 03:53.685
Hey, if you get a sword, I have a sword.

03:53.732 --> 03:54.652
We could actually have...

03:54.721 --> 03:56.487
- Can we get back to Toby?
- Sure. Sure.

03:56.556 --> 03:58.790
I'm glad he's okay, but what
are we gonna do about this?

03:58.859 --> 04:00.291
Maybe we should talk to Hunter's mom.

04:00.360 --> 04:02.861
Oh, no. That woman
is meaner than her son.

04:02.929 --> 04:04.362
Please don't tell her I said that.

04:04.431 --> 04:05.430
The solution is clear.

04:05.498 --> 04:07.031
Toby needs to learn
how to defend himself,

04:07.133 --> 04:08.533
and I would be happy to teach him.

04:08.602 --> 04:10.501
No, Rick, that is not the solution.

04:10.604 --> 04:11.569
Well, of course it is.

04:11.671 --> 04:13.104
This way,
the next time he gets picked on,

04:13.173 --> 04:15.874
he can strike back like a cobra
with lightning-quick fists.

04:15.976 --> 04:17.408
Well, cobras don't have fists, Rick.

04:17.476 --> 04:19.677
They don't need them, John.
They're nature's fist.

04:19.745 --> 04:22.196
Okay, enough.
I am firmly against fighting.

04:22.267 --> 04:23.381
I want Toby to be raised

04:23.450 --> 04:25.350
as a man of peace and non-violence.

04:25.418 --> 04:27.986
Well, as the proud principal of
a school founded by pacifists,

04:28.054 --> 04:29.921
I have to say... up top.

04:30.891 --> 04:31.990
He can stay peaceful

04:32.058 --> 04:34.659
while still learning
the fundamentals of kicking ass.

04:34.761 --> 04:35.960
I said no.

04:36.029 --> 04:37.562
John, I want Toby moved

04:37.664 --> 04:39.364
to a less aggressive English class.

04:39.432 --> 04:40.832
I don't know. They're all pretty rough.

04:40.934 --> 04:42.133
You can't do that.

04:42.202 --> 04:43.935
Because then he'll be the boy
whose aunt saved him.

04:44.004 --> 04:45.370
He'll get picked on even more.

04:45.438 --> 04:47.772
As Toby's legal guardian,
that's my decision.

04:47.874 --> 04:49.941
Because whatever happens
to Toby is on me.

04:50.043 --> 04:51.476
Hey, I care about him, too.

04:51.544 --> 04:52.677
We've really connected.

04:52.746 --> 04:55.647
We both hate snow pants
and mushrooms. He's my guy!

04:55.715 --> 04:57.382
Rick, I'm sorry,
but I have to go with the wishes

04:57.450 --> 04:58.516
of the legal guardian.

04:58.585 --> 05:01.119
I will move Toby to another class, okay?

05:01.187 --> 05:03.354
Now, if you two will excuse me,
I'd like for you to leave

05:03.423 --> 05:05.423
so that I can play with this sword.

05:05.525 --> 05:08.240
<i>Julie told Mellor not to
teach Toby about fighting,</i>

05:08.334 --> 05:10.169
<i>but, like always,
he just couldn't help himself.</i>

05:10.240 --> 05:11.262
All right, listen up!

05:11.364 --> 05:13.631
I know we're supposed to start
our kickball unit today,

05:13.733 --> 05:14.999
but Coach has called an audible,

05:15.101 --> 05:17.468
and today we'll be
diving into Taekwondo.

05:17.537 --> 05:19.570
A powerful discipline
of Korean martial arts

05:19.639 --> 05:23.247
first perfected by masters
Jong Chang and Cha Kyo Han.

05:23.310 --> 05:25.610
And then, of course,
made famous by Chuck Norris.

05:25.712 --> 05:26.978
Walker, Texas Ranger?

05:27.047 --> 05:29.514
Eh, he's more than that, Ed.
He's America's Ranger.

05:29.582 --> 05:31.616
But, Coach, Aunt Julie says
I'm not supposed to fight.

05:31.718 --> 05:32.850
And you're not.

05:32.919 --> 05:35.386
You're simply partaking
in a mandatory gym class,

05:35.455 --> 05:38.222
which today, randomly,
happens to be Taekwondo.

05:38.291 --> 05:39.724
Now, first, we will be learning

05:39.793 --> 05:42.226
how to obliterate
our opponent's rib cage,

05:42.295 --> 05:44.195
which we will simulate
with this particle board

05:44.297 --> 05:45.964
that I borrowed from the art department.

05:46.066 --> 05:47.465
Do not tell Mr. Granger.

05:47.567 --> 05:49.467
Okay. I need a volunteer.

05:50.870 --> 05:53.037
- Toby!
- He didn't even raise his hand!

05:53.106 --> 05:55.840
Ah, yes, but as Master Chang once said,

05:55.909 --> 05:59.577
the humble lotus blossom
that asks not for the rain

05:59.679 --> 06:02.513
is the first one to receive...

06:02.615 --> 06:04.082
the big drop.

06:04.184 --> 06:05.216
Get up here.

06:05.318 --> 06:06.551
Okay, Toby.

06:06.619 --> 06:09.721
You're gonna aim for a spot
past the board.

06:09.789 --> 06:11.155
All right, now focus.

06:11.257 --> 06:12.790
And strike!

06:12.892 --> 06:13.958
Hi-yah!

06:14.060 --> 06:16.294
Aah! Aah! Oh, my...

06:16.396 --> 06:17.595
You hurt your hand on this?

06:17.664 --> 06:20.131
It's basically a step above
a giant Nilla Wafer.

06:20.200 --> 06:21.432
Oh, my pinkie's puffing up.

06:21.501 --> 06:23.301
I better go see Aunt Julie
in the nurse's office.

06:23.370 --> 06:24.302
No! You can't.

06:24.404 --> 06:25.470
Uh...

06:25.572 --> 06:27.271
Because one of the first
principles of Taekwondo

06:27.374 --> 06:29.797
is we heal ourselves
without any outside help.

06:29.822 --> 06:30.752
But it hurts!

06:30.777 --> 06:33.011
We just need to find something to...

06:33.113 --> 06:35.251
immobilize it and... hide it.

06:36.606 --> 06:37.548
Perfect!

06:37.650 --> 06:39.083
Better. This might actually work.

06:39.185 --> 06:40.518
Ah, of course it'll work.

06:40.587 --> 06:44.022
As Master Chang said, "A true
warrior keeps his pain hidden...

06:44.090 --> 06:46.424
from his... aunt."

06:47.961 --> 06:49.427
<i>Marching band was over for the day,</i>

06:49.496 --> 06:51.996
<i>so I was racing back to my room
to relieve Wilma.</i>

06:52.098 --> 06:55.400
♪ And so, I wake in the morning
and I step outside ♪

06:55.468 --> 06:57.068
Thank you for covering for me.

06:57.137 --> 06:59.103
Oh, no problem. I enjoyed it.

06:59.172 --> 07:01.639
♪ And I scream
from the top of my lungs ♪

07:01.741 --> 07:03.975
♪ What's going on? ♪

07:04.077 --> 07:05.109
- Whoo! Sing it, mama!
- Sing it proud!

07:05.211 --> 07:07.278
♪ And I say hey... ♪

07:07.380 --> 07:08.813
Oh. That's okay, Jessica.

07:08.915 --> 07:10.181
You're, um, trying to belt,

07:10.283 --> 07:11.482
but you're flipping up
into your head voice.

07:11.584 --> 07:12.617
Here, let me show you.

07:12.685 --> 07:14.118
♪ And I say hey... ♪

07:15.221 --> 07:16.854
You know, I ate popcorn yesterday,

07:16.923 --> 07:18.856
and I think I got a little...
kernel stuck in there.

07:18.958 --> 07:19.957
Here we go.

07:20.060 --> 07:21.959
♪ And I say hey... ♪

07:22.028 --> 07:23.061
Nope.

07:23.163 --> 07:25.196
♪ And I say hey... ♪

07:26.633 --> 07:28.933
Uh, I think the problem is
I'm just not warmed up yet.

07:29.035 --> 07:30.768
I can show her. Here. It's like this.

07:30.870 --> 07:35.141
♪ And I say hey, yeah, yeah ♪

07:35.195 --> 07:37.675
♪ Hey, yeah, yeah ♪

07:37.777 --> 07:39.343
♪ I said hey ♪

07:39.446 --> 07:42.213
♪ What's going on? ♪

07:43.483 --> 07:44.482
Wow!

07:44.584 --> 07:45.783
Uh, I'm sorry.

07:45.852 --> 07:48.586
Is Linda Perry from
4 Non Blondes in the building?

07:48.688 --> 07:51.422
- Ms. Howell, that was awesome!
- Do you take requests?

07:51.524 --> 07:54.425
I have one... sing and don't
ever stop singing. Seriously.

07:54.527 --> 07:56.961
All right. Wilma needs to get going.

07:57.063 --> 07:58.996
You guys are so nice
to make her feel good.

07:59.099 --> 08:00.565
Not as good as she made us feel.

08:00.667 --> 08:02.934
Yeah. She's definitely
the best singer in the school.

08:03.036 --> 08:04.836
Oh. Like you've heard
everyone sing, Becky?

08:04.938 --> 08:06.471
Why are you even a science teacher?

08:06.573 --> 08:08.239
You should totally be a famous singer.

08:08.341 --> 08:09.607
I think it's safe to say

08:09.709 --> 08:11.943
that we're all better people
for having witnessed that.

08:12.045 --> 08:13.478
<i>And just like that,</i>

08:13.580 --> 08:16.747
<i>Wilma was suddenly
the rock star of the school.</i>

08:19.319 --> 08:21.586
If you're asking me for a catch,
I've been waiting for this day.

08:21.688 --> 08:23.488
I can't believe you went behind my back

08:23.590 --> 08:24.856
and taught him karate.

08:24.958 --> 08:26.090
It's Taekwondo.

08:26.192 --> 08:28.192
Completely different country.
Try to be sensitive.

08:28.294 --> 08:29.894
You know what this does, Rick?

08:29.996 --> 08:31.562
It makes me lose trust in you.

08:31.664 --> 08:34.065
I was only trying to teach Toby
how to defend himself in a fight.

08:34.167 --> 08:36.134
And I don't want Toby
to ever get in a fight.

08:36.236 --> 08:37.869
What are you gonna do...
roll him up in bubble wrap

08:37.971 --> 08:40.004
and keep him locked in his room
like some...

08:40.106 --> 08:42.405
tiny, short-haired boy Rapunzel?

08:42.509 --> 08:43.741
And what are you gonna do?

08:43.842 --> 08:46.110
Throw him into a cage match
and let him fight to the death?

08:46.212 --> 08:47.921
Well, first, I'd have him
watch "Bloodsport."

08:47.946 --> 08:48.990
Not some Norris vehicle.

08:49.015 --> 08:50.548
Jean-Claude Van Damme at his finest.

08:50.650 --> 08:52.617
Rick, stop trying to get Toby killed.

08:52.719 --> 08:54.285
I only had him
punch through some art supplies!

08:54.387 --> 08:55.753
Stop being so overprotective!

08:55.855 --> 08:57.288
Which is what I told you not to do.

08:57.390 --> 08:59.090
Stop being so under-protective!

08:59.192 --> 09:01.002
- Overprotective!
- Under-protective!

09:01.027 --> 09:02.111
- Over!
- Under!

09:02.138 --> 09:03.538
Hey, guys, I hope I'm not interrupting,

09:03.563 --> 09:06.130
but Medieval Times has one table
left for Saturday night.

09:06.158 --> 09:07.165
Are you in?

09:09.269 --> 09:11.469
I'm gonna put you down for a maybe...?

09:11.571 --> 09:12.703
Yeah?

09:13.436 --> 09:15.795
<i>I wasn't feeling like
the rock star I thought I was,</i>

09:15.868 --> 09:17.443
<i>so I was going to do what anybody</i>

09:17.514 --> 09:19.170
<i>who's threatened by
another band member would do...</i>

09:19.241 --> 09:20.373
<i>kick her ass out.</i>

09:20.475 --> 09:23.153
Hey. Thanks again
for covering Show Choir.

09:23.208 --> 09:24.440
Oh, no problem. I had a blast.

09:24.509 --> 09:26.215
I'm actually looking forward
to doing it again.

09:26.301 --> 09:27.500
You know, I can manage.

09:27.569 --> 09:29.769
You can go back
to your true passion... science.

09:29.837 --> 09:32.038
Rubber gloves and goggles
and long white coats.

09:32.106 --> 09:34.440
So, your knowledge of science
is mostly wardrobe-based.

09:34.467 --> 09:35.451
That's correct.

09:35.476 --> 09:36.642
But I thought you said you needed me

09:36.711 --> 09:37.843
to help cover Show Choir all week.

09:37.912 --> 09:39.612
Nope. I shifted some stuff around.

09:39.714 --> 09:41.480
I am gooood, good, good.

09:41.549 --> 09:43.470
Cool. I look forward to seeing the show.

09:43.495 --> 09:44.500
Okay, perfect.

09:44.525 --> 09:45.484
There's nothing I would love more

09:45.520 --> 09:48.020
than seeing you sitting quietly
in that audience.

09:48.089 --> 09:49.455
<i>With Wilma out of my spotlight,</i>

09:49.524 --> 09:51.290
<i>I got someone else to cover my class</i>

09:51.359 --> 09:53.226
<i>who I knew could never outshine me.</i>

09:55.897 --> 09:57.463
Right, guys?

09:58.800 --> 10:00.533
- Oh, hey, Lainey.
- Oh, hi!

10:00.602 --> 10:02.435
I thought you didn't need anyone
to cover Show Choir.

10:02.537 --> 10:04.637
You said you were good, good, good.

10:04.706 --> 10:06.005
See, I was good

10:06.074 --> 10:08.608
because the thing
I thought I had, I didn't have,

10:08.676 --> 10:10.743
but then the thing
I thought I didn't have...

10:10.812 --> 10:12.645
turns out, I had that thing.

10:12.714 --> 10:14.547
Lainey, what's going on?
Did I do something wrong?

10:14.616 --> 10:16.882
Now that you mention it,
I-I didn't want to bring this up,

10:16.985 --> 10:18.584
but I was getting a vibe from the kids.

10:18.686 --> 10:19.652
