14:51.432 --> 14:53.475
"It's hard to wear a lot of hats."

14:53.544 --> 14:55.578
- That says, "Hang in there!"
- Damn it!

14:55.680 --> 14:57.046
That's supposed to be a poster of a man

14:57.114 --> 14:59.281
trying to balance
a bunch of hats on his head.

14:59.383 --> 15:01.417
It was perfect for this situation.

15:01.485 --> 15:02.818
Martha.

15:02.887 --> 15:04.954
Please stop coming into my
office and changing my posters.

15:05.056 --> 15:06.889
I'm sorry. What is your point, John?

15:06.958 --> 15:09.224
What I'm saying is
I wear a lot of hats, too.

15:09.293 --> 15:11.360
Principal, friend, counselor.

15:11.429 --> 15:14.630
And all of my hats would like
to help all of your hats.

15:14.732 --> 15:15.764
Well, as my principal,

15:15.833 --> 15:17.700
can you tell the nurse
to stop treating Toby

15:17.768 --> 15:19.802
like a china doll with bird bones?

15:19.870 --> 15:22.304
And as my friend,
can you tell my boyfriend

15:22.406 --> 15:25.126
to stop trying to turn Toby
into a mini Steven Seagal?

15:25.176 --> 15:27.384
Look, guys, what I'm hearing is that

15:27.439 --> 15:29.578
- you both want what's best for Toby.
- Yes.

15:29.603 --> 15:30.847
- Of course.
- That's what I thought.

15:30.848 --> 15:32.399
- By helping him to prepare...
- By trying to keep him safe...

15:32.469 --> 15:34.183
- ...for all the challenges he'll face in life.
- ...from all the dangers he'll face in life.

15:34.285 --> 15:35.985
You know, I hear arguments
like this all the time.

15:36.087 --> 15:38.087
- When I'm dealing with parents.
- Parents?

15:38.189 --> 15:39.488
Parents with very different opinions

15:39.557 --> 15:41.056
on how a child should be raised.

15:41.158 --> 15:42.758
Well, the P-word
doesn't really apply to me,

15:42.860 --> 15:44.093
since Julie's made it very clear

15:44.195 --> 15:45.494
that she's the parent and I'm not.

15:45.596 --> 15:47.396
Rick, you act like
you're completely shut out.

15:47.498 --> 15:49.565
You're totally involved in Toby's life.

15:49.667 --> 15:51.367
Sure. Driving him around,
making his lunch,

15:51.469 --> 15:52.735
helping him with his homework.

15:52.837 --> 15:54.870
I'm basically a super-jacked nanny,

15:54.972 --> 15:57.406
and it seems to me
that's all I'll ever be.

15:59.410 --> 16:02.444
I'm sorry, Julie.
I don't know what to say.

16:02.546 --> 16:04.079
But maybe that poster does.

16:06.283 --> 16:08.617
Seems Martha knew exactly
what belonged on my wall.

16:09.934 --> 16:11.735
<i>It had been a day
since I snapped on Wilma,</i>

16:11.804 --> 16:13.121
<i>and I needed some alone time.</i>

16:13.184 --> 16:15.740
<i>But CB wasn't gonna let me have it.</i>

16:15.795 --> 16:17.459
- Hi, Lainey.
- Hey.

16:17.553 --> 16:19.388
<i>He could tell something was wrong,</i>

16:19.467 --> 16:20.848
<i>so he tried to cheer me up</i>

16:20.920 --> 16:22.987
<i>by showing off some of
those breakdancing skills</i>

16:23.056 --> 16:24.180
<i>he had been bragging about.</i>

16:24.274 --> 16:27.642
<i>Despite my lack of enthusiasm,
he just kept on trying.</i>

16:29.946 --> 16:31.723
Oh, come on, Lainey.

16:31.748 --> 16:33.308
That was my money move right there.

16:33.356 --> 16:35.690
I'm sorry. I'm just kind of
having the worst day ever.

16:35.759 --> 16:36.925
That's intense. What's wrong?

16:37.027 --> 16:38.660
Wilma's a better singer than me.

16:38.729 --> 16:39.861
That's the worst day ever?

16:39.930 --> 16:41.496
You don't get it.
I'm the one who had a band.

16:41.565 --> 16:43.531
I'm the one who once opened
for Terence Trent D'Arby.

16:43.600 --> 16:44.566
I should be the best.

16:44.634 --> 16:45.967
Look, just 'cause Wilma's a great singer

16:46.036 --> 16:47.669
doesn't make you
any less of a great singer.

16:47.738 --> 16:50.505
I know, but she's so good. It's like...

16:50.574 --> 16:52.273
Okay, seems like you have
two choices right here.

16:52.375 --> 16:53.842
You can either be jealous or petty...

16:53.910 --> 16:55.143
Oh. Well, I guess I'd go with jealous.

16:55.212 --> 16:56.303
No, that wasn't the choice.

16:56.342 --> 16:58.213
- Those were both in the first choice.
- What's the second choice?

16:58.281 --> 16:59.814
You can get over all this stuff,

16:59.850 --> 17:02.684
apologize to Wilma, and continue
with your great friendship.

17:04.087 --> 17:05.854
- Thanks, CB.
- No problem.

17:10.359 --> 17:12.359
Wow. Polishing your whistles.

17:12.462 --> 17:13.962
You must really be mad at me.

17:14.030 --> 17:16.263
Yeah, well,
polishing them does soothe me.

17:16.333 --> 17:17.632
In a way, these whistles are

17:17.701 --> 17:19.367
the only children I'll ever have, so...

17:19.469 --> 17:20.868
Rick, come on.

17:20.936 --> 17:22.837
I don't understand why you're
shutting me out of Toby's life.

17:22.939 --> 17:24.372
I'm not trying to shut you out.

17:24.441 --> 17:26.273
It's just that this
whole parenting thing

17:26.343 --> 17:27.809
is new and overwhelming for me,

17:27.877 --> 17:30.211
and I am constantly scared
that I'm gonna screw it up.

17:30.280 --> 17:31.279
Are you kidding me?

17:31.381 --> 17:33.014
Julie, you're an amazing mom.

17:33.116 --> 17:34.783
Toby is so lucky to have you.

17:34.851 --> 17:35.817
Thank you.

17:35.886 --> 17:37.919
And you don't have to do this alone.

17:38.021 --> 17:40.021
I... just didn't realize
that you wanted to be

17:40.090 --> 17:41.723
such an active part of Toby's life.

17:41.825 --> 17:43.391
Why wouldn't I want that?

17:43.460 --> 17:45.026
I told you, he's my guy.

17:45.095 --> 17:46.561
I just wasn't sure
that that's a commitment

17:46.663 --> 17:47.962
that you wanted to take on.

17:48.064 --> 17:49.030
Well, it is.

17:49.099 --> 17:50.598
It's all part of us.

17:50.667 --> 17:52.667
But I should have
respected your boundaries

17:52.736 --> 17:54.002
and not done what I did.

17:54.104 --> 17:55.270
I know that you were just doing

17:55.372 --> 17:57.505
- what you thought was best for Toby.
- Of course.

17:57.607 --> 17:58.706
That's all I'll ever do,

17:58.775 --> 18:00.975
and I know that's all you'd ever do.

18:01.044 --> 18:03.745
I think we just need to do
a better job of communicating

18:03.847 --> 18:05.413
so we can do it together.

18:06.157 --> 18:07.182
I'd like that.

18:07.284 --> 18:08.384
